Leading homecare brand, PZ Cussons  Africa has denied plan to leave the country. Chief Executive Officer (CEO) of PZ Cussons, Africa,  Mr Christos Giannopoulos stated this at the Alex-Ekwueme Federal University, Ndufu-Alike Ikwo (AE-FUNAI) Ebonyi, during the inauguration of institution’s upgraded chemical laboratory. Giannopoulos described the news as `unfounded’ and urged the public to disregard it. “I am stating categorically that we are still in Nigeria, investing and growing together with the country. “Quote me if you like, even on social media that the news is making the rounds is not correct,” he said.